            "content": "Warning Signs Requiring Immediate Electrician Attention: Contact us immediately if you experience any of these electrical warning signs: burning or plastic smell from outlets, panel, or switches (immediate fire hazard), sparking from outlets or switches when plugging in devices, breakers that won't reset after tripping, outlets or switches that feel warm or hot to touch, buzzing or humming sounds from electrical panel, frequent light flickering throughout home, discolored or melted outlet plates, any signs of smoke or scorch marks, exposed or damaged wiring, electrical shocks or tingling when touching appliances or fixtures, or GFCI outlets that won't reset. These symptoms indicate serious electrical hazards requiring professional diagnosis and repair—never ignore electrical warning signs as they often precede electrical fires or dangerous shock conditions. We provide 24/7 emergency electrical service and prioritize safety hazards with rapid response (typically within 1-2 hours)."
